  "sentences": [
    {
      "id": "ch33-01",
      "text": "Napoléon a trouvé Gustave.",
      "imagePrompt": "In a grand 1870 Parisian laboratory, Napoleon III stands beside Gustave Franklin, both facing the viewer, as the Emperor inspects a gleaming brass molecular device on the central table. Steampunk machinery fills the background. Medium shot, eye-level. Gas chandeliers cast golden light, historic and momentous mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "napoleon_gustave",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-02",
      "text": "C'est une découverte moléculaire.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "napoleon_gustave",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-03",
      "text": "Napoléon est l'Empereur.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "napoleon_gustave",
      "speaker": "Narrateur"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-04",
      "text": "Gustave est un savant.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "napoleon_gustave",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-05",
      "text": "Bazaine est le fils.",
      "imagePrompt": "In a steampunk government laboratory, Bazaine in military uniform stands at the front facing the viewer, arms behind his back, overseeing nervous scientists at their workbenches. His officer's insignia marking him as the son of power is the focal point. Medium shot, eye-level. Overhead gas lamps cast harsh light, intimidating and watchful mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "bazaine",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-06",
      "text": "La disparition a touché le monde.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "bazaine",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-07",
      "text": "Bazaine arrive avec Napoléon.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "bazaine",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-08",
      "text": "Le fils regarde les savants qui travaillent.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "bazaine",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-09",
      "text": "Le pétrole a disparu.",
      "imagePrompt": "Inside a grimy steampunk warehouse, rows of empty petroleum barrels stand drained and rusted in the foreground, while workers stack coal sacks to replace them. The empty barrels marked 'PETROLE' are the focal point. Wide shot, eye-level. Pale daylight filters through dusty windows, bleak and depleted mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "oil_gone",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-10",
      "text": "Ensuite, tout a changé.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "oil_gone",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-11",
      "text": "Le pétrole n'est plus là.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "oil_gone",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-12",
      "text": "Ensuite, le monde tombe dans la nuit.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "oil_gone",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-13",
      "text": "La découverte moléculaire change tout, mais le pétrole a disparu.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "oil_gone",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-14",
      "text": "Gustave va rentrer.",
      "imagePrompt": "At the threshold of his old laboratory, Gustave Franklin steps through the doorway facing the viewer, travel-worn coat in hand, his son waiting inside by a brass workbench. The open door framing the steampunk Paris skyline is the focal point. Medium shot, eye-level. Warm gaslight from within contrasts with grey daylight outside, relieved and hopeful mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "homecoming",
      "speaker": "Narrateur"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-15",
      "text": "Le fils de Napoléon est là.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "homecoming",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-16",
      "text": "On rentre au labo.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "homecoming",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-17",
      "text": "Il faut rentrer parce que le travail continue.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "homecoming",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-18",
      "text": "La découverte est grande.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "homecoming",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-19",
      "text": "On a touché la découverte.",
      "imagePrompt": "In the grand laboratory, Napoleon, Bazaine, and Gustave stand around a brass device facing the viewer, all three reaching toward a glowing molecular formula hovering above it. The luminous formula is the focal point. Medium shot, eye-level. The formula's glow illuminates their eager faces against gaslit walls, covetous and tense mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "touched",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-20",
      "text": "C'est moléculaire, dit Gustave.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "touched",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-21",
      "text": "On touche le monde.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "touched",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-22",
      "text": "On touche la disparition lorsqu'on regarde le monde.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "touched",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-23",
      "text": "Bazaine a tout vu ensuite.",
      "imagePrompt": "In a gaslit corridor, Bazaine watches from a doorway facing the viewer, his expression cold and knowing, as an empty laboratory with an abandoned workbench is visible behind him. A single scientist's coat left draped over a chair is the focal point. Medium shot, eye-level. A gas wall sconce lights Bazaine's face, ominous and conspiratorial mood.",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "legacy",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-24",
      "text": "La disparition des savants continue.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "teaching",
      "group": "legacy",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-25",
      "text": "Napoléon regarde Bazaine qui a tout vu.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "legacy",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-26",
      "text": "Bazaine est le fils qui connaît la disparition.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
      "readings": [],
      "type": "flow",
      "group": "legacy",
      "speaker": "Avril"
    },
    {
      "id": "ch33-27",
      "text": "Le pétrole a disparu du monde parce que les savants ont disparu.",
      "imagePrompt": "",
